---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
// Wildlife Rescue Platform — Case Study
---

<style>
  .project-header {
    margin: 0;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .page__title {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    width: 100%;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--clr-brand-blue);
  }

  .section__container {
    margin: 40px auto 80px;
    max-width: 820px;
  }
  
  .section__title {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .section__intro {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 8px 0 8px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #444;
  }

  .section__subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .section__list {
    margin: 16px 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
}

.section__list.--parent {
    background-color: #fff7ed;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px 40px;
    border: 1px solid var(--clr-brand-orange);
  }
  
  .section__item {
    margin: 6px 0;
    list-style: disc;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ✨ subtle section separation */
  .section__container + .section__container {
    border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    padding-top: 40px;
  }

  /* ✨ improve readability for dense content */
  p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ✨ better code block spacing */
  pre {
    margin: 16px 0;
    padding: 12px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #111;
    color: #eee;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
</style>

<Layout> 
  <div class="relative z-50 col-start-2 col-span-10 max-sm:col-start-3 max-sm:col-span-9">

    <header class="project-header">
      <h1 class="page__title">Wildlife Rescue & Operations Platform</h1>
      <p class="page__subtitle">Solutions Engineering & System Design</p>
    </header>

    <!-- 1. Problem & Goals -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">1. Problem & Goals</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">Wildlife rescue efforts are hindered by fragmented coordination, delayed response times, and inconsistent data handling across multiple actors. The goal is to streamline operations, improve response efficiency, ensure data reliability, and increase transparency and engagement while maintaining high system availability.</p>


      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Wildlife rescue efforts suffer from fragmented coordination, delayed responses, and inconsistent data</li>
        <li class="section__item">Operational challenges:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Delays caused by unstructured reporting (phone, social media)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Lack of centralized, real-time operational visibility</li>
            <li class="section__item">Volunteer coordination is inefficient and error-prone</li>
            <li class="section__item">Medical records are inconsistent and not standardized</li>
            <li class="section__item">Donation tracking lacks transparency, reducing trust</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Goals:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Reduce response time (&lt; 2h from 4–6h)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Increase volunteer participation (&gt; 75%)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Ensure &gt; 90% data completeness</li>
            <li class="section__item">Improve donation transparency (&gt; 90% traceability)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Increase public engagement (&gt; 60%)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Maintain system uptime &gt; 99%</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Context & Constraints -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">2. Context & Constraints</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">The system operates within a complex, multi-actor environment involving citizens, NGOs, volunteers, and authorities, with real-world, non-linear workflows. It must be built under technical and operational constraints such as a modular monolith architecture, limited resources, and a small team, while ensuring practicality and adoption.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Environment:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Multi-actor ecosystem (citizens, NGOs, volunteers, authorities)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Real-world, non-linear rescue workflows</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Technical constraints:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Modular monolith architecture</li>
            <li class="section__item">MongoDB (flexible schema)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Limited external integrations</li>
            <li class="section__item">Cloud-agnostic design</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Operational constraints:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Small engineering team (solo-driven)</li>
            <li class="section__item">MVP scope limited to core modules</li>
            <li class="section__item">Timeline: 6–12 months</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Assumptions:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Users have internet access</li>
            <li class="section__item">NGOs adopt system if efficiency improves</li>
            <li class="section__item">Transparency increases engagement</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: User / Actor Diagram (optional)]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Users & Requirements -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">3. Users & Requirements</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">The platform supports diverse user roles with distinct responsibilities, requiring a balance between flexibility and structured workflows. It must provide core operational capabilities while meeting performance, security, scalability, and usability requirements for real-world usage.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Users:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">General users (report incidents, track updates)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Volunteers (join and execute tasks)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Organization staff (manage operations and records)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Donors (fund and track campaigns)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Admins (system control and monitoring)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Authorities (analytics and compliance)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Functional requirements:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident reporting and tracking</li>
            <li class="section__item">Operations and medical management</li>
            <li class="section__item">Campaign and donation tracking</li>
            <li class="section__item">User management with RBAC</li>
            <li class="section__item">Notifications system</li>
            <li class="section__item">Analytics dashboards</li>
            <li class="section__item">External API integrations</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Non-functional requirements:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Performance: &lt; 3s response time</li>
            <li class="section__item">Scalability: 10,000+ concurrent users</li>
            <li class="section__item">Security: RBAC, TLS, encryption at rest</li>
            <li class="section__item">Availability: &gt; 99.5% uptime</li>
            <li class="section__item">Data integrity: consistent and auditable</li>
            <li class="section__item">Accessibility: multilingual, WCAG compliant</li>
            <li class="section__item">Maintainability: modular structure</li>
            <li class="section__item">Auditability: full change tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: User / Actor Diagram (optional)]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. System Overview -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">4. System Overview</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">The platform is a centralized web-based system designed to connect stakeholders and support end-to-end wildlife rescue operations, from incident reporting to resolution, while also enabling campaign management and analytics.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Web-based platform connecting users, organizations, and authorities</li>
        <li class="section__item">Capabilities:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident reporting</li>
            <li class="section__item">Rescue operations management</li>
            <li class="section__item">Medical tracking</li>
            <li class="section__item">Donation campaigns</li>
            <li class="section__item">Analytics dashboards</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">External integrations:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Payment gateways</li>
            <li class="section__item">Partner APIs</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">System prioritizes operational effectiveness over rigid workflows</li>
        <li class="section__item">Core flows:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident → Report → Operation → Resolution</li>
            <li class="section__item">Campaign → Donation → Tracking</li>
            <li class="section__item">User → Role → Permissions</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: C1 – System Context Diagram]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. Architecture -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">5. Architecture</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">The system uses a modular monolith architecture to separate concerns across clearly defined components, ensuring maintainability, control, and efficient development while supporting core operational modules.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Modular monolith architecture</li>
        <li class="section__item">Components:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Frontend (Astro)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Backend API (Go)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Database (MongoDB)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Cache (Redis)</li>
            <li class="section__item">File storage (Cloud storage)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Communication:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">REST APIs</li>
            <li class="section__item">JSON-based contracts</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Core modules:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Auth / Identity</li>
            <li class="section__item">Profile</li>
            <li class="section__item">Organization / Team</li>
            <li class="section__item">Incident / Report</li>
            <li class="section__item">Operations (Field + Medical)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Animal</li>
            <li class="section__item">Campaign / Donation</li>
            <li class="section__item">Notification</li>
            <li class="section__item">Audit</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: C2 – Container Diagram]</p>
      <p>[Diagram: C3 – Component Diagram (optional)]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Data Model & Behavior -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">6. Data Model & Behavior</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">A structured and flexible data model underpins the system, enabling consistent data handling, traceability, and support for complex workflows, with clearly defined entities, relationships, and lifecycle behaviors.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Core entities:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident, Report, MasterReport</li>
            <li class="section__item">FieldOperation, MedicalOperation</li>
            <li class="section__item">Animal</li>
            <li class="section__item">Campaign, Donation</li>
            <li class="section__item">Organization, Team, User</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Aggregation model:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Report → MasterReport → MegaReport</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Data rules:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">No hard deletes (auditability)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Derived fields (risk level, campaign progress)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Time constraints (≤ 365 days)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">RBAC:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Membership roles (Manager, Contributor)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Functional roles (Vet, Ranger)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Entity-level roles (Operation Lead)</li>
            <li class="section__item">System roles (Admin)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Key workflows:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident submission → validation → report creation</li>
            <li class="section__item">Report → operation assignment → execution</li>
            <li class="section__item">Campaign → donation → tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Lifecycle states:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Incident: Unverified → Resolved</li>
            <li class="section__item">Report: Draft → Closed</li>
            <li class="section__item">Operation: Unassigned → Completed</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: ER / Data Model Diagram]</p>
      <p>[Diagram: Sequence Diagram (optional)]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. Decisions & Trade-offs -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">7. Decisions & Trade-offs</h2>
     <p class="section__intro">Key architectural decisions prioritize simplicity, maintainability, and delivery speed over premature scalability, with explicit trade-offs made to balance flexibility, control, and system complexity.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Modular monolith vs microservices:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Chosen for simplicity and fast iteration</li>
            <li class="section__item">Trade-off: limited scalability</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">MongoDB vs SQL:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Chosen for flexible and evolving schemas</li>
            <li class="section__item">Trade-off: weaker analytical querying</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">REST vs GraphQL:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Chosen for simplicity and standardization</li>
            <li class="section__item">Trade-off: less flexible data fetching</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Stateful auth vs JWT:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Chosen for control and revocation</li>
            <li class="section__item">Trade-off: session management overhead</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">General principle:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Prioritize simplicity, maintainability, and delivery speed over premature scale</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Reliability & Scalability -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">8. Reliability & Scalability</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">The system ensures reliability through validation, access control, and audit mechanisms, while supporting scalable growth through caching and future-ready architectural improvements.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Reliability:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Input validation and error handling</li>
            <li class="section__item">RBAC enforcement per request</li>
            <li class="section__item">Audit logs for all critical actions</li>
            <li class="section__item">Backup-based recovery</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Availability:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Target &gt; 99.5% uptime</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Scalability:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Horizontal scaling (future-ready)</li>
            <li class="section__item">Redis for caching and rate limiting</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Limitations:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">No auto-scaling or multi-region failover</li>
            <li class="section__item">No full observability stack</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Future improvements:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Event-driven architecture</li>
            <li class="section__item">Data sharding</li>
            <li class="section__item">Advanced monitoring and alerting</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>[Diagram: Scaling Diagram (optional)]</p>
      <p>[Diagram: Failure Flow Diagram (optional)]</p>
    </section>

    <!-- 9. Outcome & Learnings -->
    <section class="section__container">
      <h2 class="section__title">9. Outcome & Learnings</h2>
      <p class="section__intro">The platform improves operational efficiency, data consistency, and coordination, while highlighting the importance of designing for real-world workflows, making explicit trade-offs, and building systems that can evolve into scalable platforms.</p>

      <ul class="section__list --parent">
        <li class="section__item">Impact:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Response time reduced to &lt; 2 hours</li>
            <li class="section__item">Volunteer participation &gt; 75%</li>
            <li class="section__item">Data completeness &gt; 90%</li>
            <li class="section__item">Improved transparency and trust</li>
            <li class="section__item">Centralized operational visibility</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Outcome:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Strong domain modeling</li>
            <li class="section__item">Clear modular architecture</li>
            <li class="section__item">Balanced trade-offs for real-world constraints</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class="section__item">Learnings:
          <ul class="section__list">
            <li class="section__item">Design for real workflows, not ideal ones</li>
            <li class="section__item">Structure NoSQL data carefully for predictability</li>
            <li class="section__item">Make explicit trade-offs</li>
            <li class="section__item">Communicate architecture clearly</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>